''See also [[safe]]''

==English==
===Combining form===
'''-safe'''
# [[Void]] from [[danger]] or commonly associated problems.
#*'''2000''' September 6, Hadley Stern and David Lehn, ''Death of the '''Websafe''' Color Palette?'', Webmonkey
#*:''But it's been more than three years since Lynda Weinman assembled her "'''browser safe''' palette" for Photoshop''
#*'''2005''', Planet Innovation, website
#*:''attempting to compile a complete list of the most '''people-safe''' products''

====Usage notes====
*Words formed using this combining form are either hyphenated ("people-safe") or single words ("Websafe") but never two words.

